=== Uncapping ===
Uncapping is the process for upgrading an augment's rarity and can only be done for upgrading a +10 Rare blue Augment into its base (+0) Elite purple version. To start, enhance the desired Rare blue Augment type to +10, plus 750XP on top of that. The Augment may then be Uncapped for 1000 {{coin}} and 2 Augmentation Cores. For an existing Augment, select it in Depot or from the ship it is equipped on and choose Enhance.

=== Conversion ===
[[File:Augment Module Conversion UI.png|350px|thumb|right|Augment Module Conversion Interface]]
Every Augment Module stat has 2 parts: 
* A fixed stat value that improves with the Augment Module's [[Augmentation#Crafting_and_Enhancing|Enhancement Level]].
* A conversion stat value between 1 and the conversion stat's predetermined maximum value.
** The [[Ultra Rainbow Hammer]] and all collaboration-exclusive Unique Augments Modules do '''not''' have conversion stats. The game lists their conversion stat as "+ 0", and you cannot perform Conversion on them.

The <u>'''conversion stat'''</u> can be improved by using Augment Module Conversion Stones [[File:T1 Augment Module Conversion Stone.png|30px|link=]] [[File:T2 Augment Module Conversion Stone.png|30px|link=]]. 

To do this, select an Augment Module then select Conversion. This costs 1 Conversion Stone per roll. Whenever a Conversion Stone is used, the resulting outcome will '''always''' be an improvement. The amount of improvement is randomly chosen. Once the conversion stats reach their maximum values, you cannot perform Conversion on that Augment Module anymore.

Common Augment Modules use T1 (Elite) Conversion stones, while Unique Augment Modules use T2 (Super Rare) Conversion stones.

== Drop Locations for Augmentation Materials ==
Augmentation materials can be acquired in the following ways:

*Limited events, like [[Operation Convergence]] or [[Special Support Plan Augment Modules]].
*The [[Daily_Raid#Module_Development|Module Development "Daily" Raid]] allows you to gather Rare Augment Modules, Augment Module Stones, Augment Module Cores and Augment Module Conversion Stones twice a week.
*Higher campaign chapters (12 and up) can drop Augment Module Stones as clearing rewards.
*The [[Operation_Siren#Arbiter|Arbiter (Normal) battles in Operation Siren]] drop Augment Module Cores.
*The [[Cruise Missions]] provide Augment Module Cores and Augment Module Stones, with additional ones available in the Fair Winds Cruise Pass.

